    • Constructor Detail

      • StdAttributeAssignment

        public StdAttributeAssignment(AttributeAssignment attributeAssignment)
        Creates a new immutable StdAttributeAssignment that wraps the given AttributeAssignment. The caller agrees not to modify the given AttributeAssignment as long as the new StdAttributeAssignment refers to it.
        Parameters:
        attributeAssignment - the AttributeAssignment to be wrapped by the new StdAttributeAssignment.

      • StdAttributeAssignment

        public StdAttributeAssignment(Identifier categoryIn,
                      Identifier attributeIdIn,
                      java.lang.String issuerIn,
                      AttributeValue<?> attributeValueIn)
        Creates a new immutable StdAttributeAssignment with the given Identifiers representing the XACML Category and AttributeId of the Attribute to be assigned, the given String issuer, and the given AttributeValue representing the value to assign to the Attribute.
        Parameters:
        categoryIn - the Identifier representing the Category of the Attribute to be assigned
        attributeIdIn - the Identifier representing the AttributeId of the Attribute to be assigned
        issuerIn - the String representing the Issuer of the Attribute to be assigned
        attributeValueIn - the AttributeValue representing the AttributeValue to be assigned to the Attribute
